                    "body": "It's because Arrow string arrays have a 2 GiB limit due to the representation (each element is represented by 32-bit signed offsets into a backing buffer); you can cast to large_string first to avoid this (this uses 64-bit offsets) but I think the error here could be much improved (it should at least tell you what to do)",
